{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["occ"],"tokens":[{"text":"@property","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" (","kind":"text"},{"text":"nonatomic","kind":"keyword"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"assign","kind":"keyword"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"getter","kind":"keyword"},{"text":"=","kind":"text"},{"text":"isDraggable","kind":"identifier"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"text":"BOOL","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@BOOL","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"draggable","kind":"identifier"},{"text":";","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["iOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","anchor":"discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If this property is set to ","type":"text"},{"code":"YES","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", the user can drag the annotation after","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"pressing and holding the view, and the associated annotation object must also","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"implement the ","type":"text"},{"code":"setCoordinate:","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" method. The default value of this property is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"NO","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Setting this property to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"YES"},{"type":"text","text":" lets the map view know that the annotation is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"always draggable. In other words, you cannot conditionalize drag operations by"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"attempting to stop an operation that has already been initiated; doing so can"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"lead to undefined behavior. Once begun, the drag operation should always"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"continue to completion."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":4,"text":"Related examples","type":"heading","anchor":"Related-examples"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"TODO: Enable users to drag "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" objects on your map."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview\/draggable"]}],"metadata":{"fragments":[{"text":"draggable","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"draggable","symbolKind":"property","remoteSource":{"fileName":"MLNAnnotationView.h","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/maplibre\/maplibre-native\/blob\/main\/platform\/ios\/src\/MLNAnnotationView.h#L261"},"modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"draggable","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","externalID":"c:objc(cs)MLNAnnotationView(py)draggable","roleHeading":"Instance Property"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A Boolean value indicating whether the annotation view is draggable."}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView"]]},"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"occ","url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView\/draggable"},"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotation":{"type":"topic","title":"MLNAnnotation","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol is used to provide annotation-related information"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to a map view. To use this protocol, you adopt it in any custom objects that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"store or represent annotation data. Each object then serves as the source of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"information about a single map annotation and provides critical information,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"such as the annotation’s location on the map. Annotation objects do not provide"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the visual representation of the annotation but typically coordinate (in","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"conjunction with the map view’s delegate) the creation of an appropriate","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"objects to handle the display.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotation","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNAnnotation"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"title":"MapLibre","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling."}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","role":"collection"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotationView/draggable":{"fragments":[{"text":"draggable","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"draggable","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview\/draggable","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView\/draggable","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A Boolean value indicating whether the annotation view is draggable."}],"kind":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotationView":{"fragments":[{"text":"MLNAnnotationView","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"MLNAnnotationView","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview","type":"topic","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" class is responsible for marking a point annotation","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with a view. Annotation views represent an annotation object, which is an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"object that corresponds to the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" protocol. When an annotation’s","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"geographic coordinate is visible in the map view, the map view asks its","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"delegate to a corresponding annotation view. If an annotation view is created"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with a reuse identifier, the map view may recycle the view when it goes"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"offscreen."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView"}}}